properties.headline: Winter Storm Watch issued January 9 at 3:09PM CST until January 12 at 6:00AM CST by NWS Milwaukee/Sullivan WI
properties.description:
...POTENTIAL WINTER STORM THIS WEEKEND...

* WHAT...Mixed precipitation is expected Friday evening and Friday
night. Precipitation will change to all snow by late Saturday
afternoon and Saturday night. Ice accumulation between a glaze
and two tenths of an inch are possible Friday evening through
Saturday morning. Snow and sleet accumulation Friday evening
through Saturday morning between 1 and 2 inches is expected.
Moderate snowfall is expected to move into the region Saturday
afternoon through Saturday night. Storm total snow accumulations
of 5 to 10 inches is possible. In addition northeast winds
could gust as high as 45 mph Saturday afternoon through Saturday
night.

* WHERE...Portions of south central and southeast Wisconsin.
Generally along and southeast of a line from Janesville to
Milwaukee.

* WHEN...The Winter Storm Watch is from Friday evening through
Saturday night.

* IMPACTS...A Winter Storm Watch means there is a potential for
significant snow...sleet...or ice accumulations that may impact
travel. Continue to monitor the latest forecasts.
properties.instruction: Monitor the latest forecasts for updates on this situation.

NWSheadline: WINTER STORM WATCH IN EFFECT FROM FRIDAY EVENING THROUGH LATE SATURDAY NIGHT
